{"id":"1902.02646","submitter":"Chula Jayawardene","authors":"Chula J. Jayawardene, W. Chandanie W. Navaratna and J.N. Senadheera","title":"All Ramsey $(C_n,K_6)$ critical graphs for large $n$","comments":"14 pages, 4 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  Let $G$ and $H$ be finite graphs. If for any two-coloring of the edges of a\ncomplete graph $K_n$, there is a copy of $G$ in the first color, red, or a copy\nof $H$ in the second color, blue, we will say $K_n\\rightarrow (G,H)$. The\nRamsey number $r(G, H)$ is defined as the smallest positive integer $n$ such\nthat $K_{n} \\rightarrow (G, H)$. A two-coloring of $K_{r(G, H)-1}$ such that\n$K_{r(G, H)-1} \\not \\rightarrow (G,H)$ is called a critical coloring. A Ramsey\ncritical $r(G, H)$ graph is a graph induced by the first color of a critical\ncoloring. In this paper, when $n \\geq 15$, we show that there exist exactly\nsixty eight non-isomorphic Ramsey critical $r(C_n, K_6)$ graphs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Feb 2019 20:34:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 9 Jun 2019 03:51:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 15 Sep 2020 11:54:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-16"}
